Variations: "Aria")

22:24.570 --> 22:27.778
(crying)
- Please.

22:34.080 --> 22:36.071
Thank you.

22:40.190 --> 22:43.489
I hate being this neurotic.
- If you weren't neurotic,

22:43.530 --> 22:47.057
Franklyn, you would be something
much worse.

22:54.200 --> 22:57.909
Our brain is designed
to experience anxiety
in short bursts,

22:57.940 --> 23:01.637
not the prolonged duress
yours has seemed to enjoy.

23:01.680 --> 23:05.172
That's why you feel as though
a lion were on the verge
of devouring you.

23:05.210 --> 23:08.077
(crying)

23:08.120 --> 23:10.441
Franklyn.
- Yes.

23:10.490 --> 23:13.550
- You have to convince yourself
the lion is not in the room.

23:13.590 --> 23:15.558
When it is,

23:15.590 --> 23:18.024
I assure you,

23:18.060 --> 23:19.857
you will know.

23:24.770 --> 23:27.568
- Dr. Lecter.
I'm, uh, Special Ag--

23:27.600 --> 23:30.569
- I hate to be discourteous,
but this is a private exit
for my patients.

23:30.610 --> 23:35.206
- Oh, Dr. Lecter.
Sorry. Um,

23:35.240 --> 23:37.105
I'm, uh, Special Agent

23:37.140 --> 23:39.938
Jack Crawford, FBI.
May I come in?

23:39.980 --> 23:41.948
- You may wait
in the waiting room.

23:41.980 --> 23:43.948
Franklyn, I'll see you
next week.

23:43.990 --> 23:46.140
- Yes.
- Unless, of course,

23:46.190 --> 23:47.714
this is about him.

23:47.760 --> 23:50.012
- No, this is all about you.

23:58.600 --> 24:00.830
- Please, come in.

24:04.240 --> 24:05.798
So,

24:05.840 --> 24:08.104
may I ask how this is
all about me?

24:08.140 --> 24:10.779
- You can ask,
but I may have to ask you

24:10.810 --> 24:13.540
a few questions first.

24:13.580 --> 24:15.639
You expecting another patient?

24:15.680 --> 24:17.170
- We're all alone.

24:17.220 --> 24:19.882
- Oh, good.

24:19.920 --> 24:22.252
No secretary?
- Was predispositioned

24:22.290 --> 24:25.748
to romantic whims.
Followed her heart
to the United Kingdom.

24:25.790 --> 24:28.554
(Jack chuckles.)
Sad to see her go.

24:31.900 --> 24:33.629
- Wow.

24:37.670 --> 24:40.138
Are these yours, Doctor?
- Among the first.

24:40.170 --> 24:42.832
My boarding school in Paris
when I was a boy.

24:42.880 --> 24:45.041
- The amount of detail is
incredible.

24:45.080 --> 24:46.877
- I learned very early

24:46.910 --> 24:49.743
a scalpel cuts better points
than a pencil sharpener.

24:49.780 --> 24:52.510
- Well, now I understand
why your drawings earned you

24:52.550 --> 24:54.609
an internship
at Johns Hopkins.

24:56.220 --> 24:58.780
- I'm beginning to suspect
you're investigating me,

24:58.830 --> 25:02.618
Agent Crawford.
- (chuckling): No, no.

25:02.660 --> 25:05.720
No, you were referred to me
by Alana Bloom

25:05.770 --> 25:09.069
in the psychology department--
Georgetown.

25:09.100 --> 25:12.069
- Most psychology departments
are filled with personality

25:12.110 --> 25:15.534
deficients. Dr. Bloom would be
the exception.

25:15.580 --> 25:17.775
- Yes, she would.
Yes, she would.

25:17.810 --> 25:21.746
Well, she told me
that you mentored her during
her residency at Johns Hopkins.

25:21.780 --> 25:23.919
- I learned as much from her
as she did from me.

25:23.950 --> 25:26.009
- Yes, but she also showed me,
uh, your paper,

25:26.050 --> 25:27.950
"Evolutionary..." uh,

25:27.990 --> 25:30.208
"Evolutionary Origins
of Social Exclusion"?

25:30.260 --> 25:31.818
- Yes.

25:31.860 --> 25:33.999
- Very interesting.
Very interesting.

25:34.030 --> 25:35.622
Even for a layman.

25:35.660 --> 25:37.924
- A layman?
- Yeah.

25:37.970 --> 25:41.098
- So many learned fellows
going about in the halls
of Behavioral Science

25:41.140 --> 25:45.167
at the FBI, and you
consider yourself a layman.
- I do when I'm in your company,

25:45.210 --> 25:47.974
doctor. Um,

25:48.010 --> 25:51.707
I need you to help me
with a psychological profile.

25:54.820 --> 25:57.175
- (Lecter): Tell me, then,
how many confessions?

25:57.220 --> 25:59.745
- Twelve dozen, the last time
I checked. None of them had

25:59.790 --> 26:02.111
any details--
until this morning.

26:02.160 --> 26:04.628
And then
they all had details.

26:04.660 --> 26:07.959
Some genius in Duluth PD
took a photograph of
Elise Nichols' body

26:08.000 --> 26:10.298
with his cell phone,
shared it with his friends,

26:10.330 --> 26:11.797
and then Freddy Lounds

26:11.830 --> 26:14.162
posted it
on Tattlecrime.com.

26:14.200 --> 26:15.736
- Tasteless.

26:15.770 --> 26:19.206
- (Lecter): Do you have
trouble with taste?

26:19.240 --> 26:21.800
- My thoughts are often
not tasty.

26:21.840 --> 26:24.343
- Nor mine.

26:24.380 --> 26:26.871
No effective barriers.
- I build forts.

26:26.910 --> 26:30.141
- Associations come quickly.
- So do forts.

26:34.290 --> 26:36.611
- Not fond of eye contact,
are you?

26:36.660 --> 26:38.628
- Eyes are distracting--

26:38.660 --> 26:41.094
you see too much,
you don't see enough.

26:41.130 --> 26:44.668
And-And it's hard to focus
when you're thinking, um,

26:44.700 --> 26:46.895
"Oh, those whites are
really white",

26:46.930 --> 26:50.058
or, "He must have hepatitis":
or, "Oh, is that a burst

26:50.100 --> 26:53.729
vein?" So, yeah,

26:53.780 --> 26:55.998
I try to avoid eyes
whenever possible.

26:56.040 --> 26:58.349
Jack?
- Yes?

26:58.380 --> 27:00.405
- I imagine what you see
and learn touches

27:00.450 --> 27:02.418
everything else
in your mind.

27:02.450 --> 27:04.418
Your values and decency are
present

27:04.450 --> 27:06.839
yet shocked
at your associations,

27:06.890 --> 27:10.018
appalled at your dreams.

27:10.060 --> 27:13.279
No forts in the bone _arena
of your skull for things
youlove.

27:13.330 --> 27:16.857
- Whose profile
are you working on?

27:16.900 --> 27:19.221
Whose profile
is he working on?

27:19.270 --> 27:22.330
- I'm sorry, Will.
Observing is what we do.

27:22.370 --> 27:24.736
I can't shut mine off any more
than you can shut yours off.

27:24.770 --> 27:27.705
- Please,
don't psychoanalyze me.

27:27.740 --> 27:30.231
You won't like me
when I'm psychoanalyzed.

27:30.280 --> 27:32.168
_ - Will.
- Now, If you'll excuse me,

27:32.210 --> 27:35.748
I have to go give a lecture
on psychoanalyzing.

27:38.750 --> 27:40.718
- Maybe we shouldn't poke him
like that,

27:40.760 --> 27:44.958
Doctor. Perhaps a less,
uh, direct approach.

27:44.990 --> 27:48.426
- What he has is
pure empathy.

27:48.460 --> 27:50.769
He can assume
your pomt of View,

27:50.800 --> 27:52.893
or mine, and maybe some other
points of view that scare him.

27:52.930 --> 27:57.435
It's an uncomfortable gift,
Jack.

27:57.470 --> 28:01.179
Perception's a tool
that's pointed on both ends.

28:01.210 --> 28:06.705
This cannibal you have him
getting to know...

28:06.750 --> 28:09.344
Ithink I can help
good Will see his face.

28:14.190 --> 28:16.750
(cawing)

28:30.770 --> 28:34.206
- (Jack): Stag head was reported
stolen last night, about a mile
from here.

28:34.240 --> 28:35.832
- Just the head?

28:35.880 --> 28:37.939
- Minneapolis Homicide's
already made a statement.

28:37.980 --> 28:40.141
They're calling him
the Minnesota Shrike.

28:40.180 --> 28:41.738
- Like the bird?

28:41.780 --> 28:45.887
- Shrike's a perching bird.
Impales mice

28:45.920 --> 28:48.480
and lizards on thorny branches
and barbed wire.

28:48.520 --> 28:51.227
Rips their organs
right out of their bodies,

28:51.260 --> 28:54.229
puts them in a little birdie
pantry, and eats them later.

28:54.260 --> 28:56.353
- I can't tell
whether it's sloppy

28:56.400 --> 28:58.868
or shrewd.
- He wanted her found

28:58.900 --> 29:00.936
this way.

29:00.970 --> 29:02.267
It's...

29:02.300 --> 29:05.303
it's petulant.

29:05.340 --> 29:08.207
I almost feel
like he's mocking her.

29:08.240 --> 29:11.107
Or... he's mocking us.

29:13.380 --> 29:15.871
- Where did all his love go?

29:15.920 --> 29:20.482
- Whoever tucked Elise Nichols
into bed didn't paint
this picture.

29:20.520 --> 29:24.456
- He took her lungs.

29:24.490 --> 29:26.981
I'm pretty sure she was alive
when he cut 'em out.

29:42.440 --> 29:45.341
- Our cannibal loves women.

29:45.380 --> 29:48.349
He doesn't want to destroy them;
he wants to consume them,

29:48.380 --> 29:51.213
to keep some part
of them inside.

29:51.250 --> 29:53.309
This girl's killer thought
that she was a pig.

29:53.350 --> 29:56.956
- You think this was a copycat?
- The cannibal

29:56.990 --> 29:58.958
who killed Elise Nichols had
a place to do it

29:58.990 --> 30:02.596
and no interest in...
in field kabuki. So,

30:02.630 --> 30:05.360
he has a house, or two,
or a-a cabin--

30:05.400 --> 30:07.937
something
with an antler room.

30:14.480 --> 30:17.847
He has a daughter.

30:17.880 --> 30:21.270
The same age as the other girls.
Same-same hair colour,

30:21.320 --> 30:23.311
same eye colour, same height,
same weight.

30:26.190 --> 30:29.512
She's an only child.
She's leaving home.

30:31.530 --> 30:34.522
He can't stand the thought
of losing her.

30:36.530 --> 30:38.566
She's his golden ticket.

30:38.600 --> 30:41.569
- What about the copycat?

30:41.600 --> 30:43.636
- You know,
an intelligent psychopath,

30:43.670 --> 30:46.503
particularly a sadist,
is very hard to catch.

30:46.540 --> 30:48.508
There's no traceable motive,
there'll be no patterns.

30:48.540 --> 30:50.531
He may never kill
this way again.

30:50.580 --> 30:52.605
Have Dr. Lecter draw up
a psychological profile.

30:52.650 --> 30:55.448
You seemed very impressed
with his opinion.

31:37.620 --> 31:39.622
(knocking on door)

31:41.630 --> 31:43.598
(blankets shuffling)

31:43.630 --> 31:45.621
(footsteps)

31:48.600 --> 31:52.309
- Good morning, Will.
May I come in?

31:52.340 --> 31:55.400
- Where's Crawford?
- Deposed in court.

31:55.440 --> 31:59.149
The adventure will be yours
and mine today.

31:59.180 --> 32:00.909
May I come in?

32:09.520 --> 32:12.455
I'm very careful
about what I put into my body,

32:12.490 --> 32:15.618
which means I end up
preparing most meals myself.

32:15.660 --> 32:19.528
A little protein scramble
to start the day.

32:19.570 --> 32:22.562
Some eggs, some sausage.

32:29.040 --> 32:30.598
- Mm, it's delicious.

32:30.640 --> 32:33.245
Thank you.
- My pleasure.

32:36.320 --> 32:39.209
I would apologize
for my analytical ambush,

32:39.250 --> 32:41.753
but I know_ I_ will soon be
apologizmg again

32:41.790 --> 32:44.224
and you'll tire of that
eventually,

32:44.260 --> 32:47.479
_so I have to consider
usmg apologies sparingly.
- Just keep it professional.

32:47.530 --> 32:52.069
- Or we could socialize,
like adults.

32:52.100 --> 32:54.068
God forbid we become friendly.

32:54.100 --> 32:56.432
- I don't find you
that interesting.

32:56.470 --> 32:58.529
- You will.

33:05.450 --> 33:08.442
Agent Crawford tells me you have
a knack for the monsters.

33:10.450 --> 33:13.248
- I don't think the Shrike
killed that girl

33:13.290 --> 33:14.689
in the field.

33:17.590 --> 33:19.751
- The devil is in the details.

33:19.790 --> 33:23.123
What didn't your copycat do
to the girl in the field?
What gave it away?

33:23.160 --> 33:25.367
- Everything.

33:25.400 --> 33:32.033
It's like he had to show me
a negative so that I could
see the positive. It...

33:32.070 --> 33:34.436
That crime_scene was
practically gift-wrapped.

33:34.480 --> 33:37.506
- The mathematics
of human behaviour--

33:37.540 --> 33:39.508
all those ugly variables.

33:39.550 --> 33:44.283
Some bad math
with this Shrike fellow, huh?

33:44.320 --> 33:47.289
Are you reconstructing
his fantasies?

33:47.320 --> 33:49.288
- Heh.
- What kind of problems

33:49.320 --> 33:51.322
does he have?
- Uh, he has a few.

33:53.690 --> 33:56.625
- You ever have any problems,
Will?

33:56.660 --> 33:58.662
- No.

33:58.700 --> 34:00.429
- Of course you don't.

34:00.470 --> 34:02.688
You and I are just alike--

34:02.740 --> 34:04.708
problem-free. Nothing about us

34:04.740 --> 34:07.766
to feel horrible about.

34:09.780 --> 34:12.749
You know, Will...

34:12.780 --> 34:16.238
I think Uncle Jack sees you
as a fragile little teacup.

34:16.280 --> 34:20.387
The finest china,
used for only special guests.

34:20.420 --> 34:24.322
(Will laughing)

34:26.790 --> 34:28.690
- How do you see me?

34:33.170 --> 34:37.163
- The mongoose
I want under the house
when the snakes slither by.

34:40.810 --> 34:42.801
Finish your breakfast.

34:49.480 --> 34:52.085
- (Will): What are you
smiling at?

34:54.320 --> 34:56.811
- Peeking behind the curtain.

34:56.860 --> 35:01.752
I'm just curious how the FBI
goes about its business when
it's not kicking in doors.

35:01.800 --> 35:05.224
- You're lucky we're not doing
house-to-house interviews.

35:05.270 --> 35:07.625
We found a little piece of metal
in Elise Nichols' clothes--

35:07.670 --> 35:10.389
a shred from a pipe threader.

35:10.440 --> 35:15.230
- There must be hundreds
of construction sites
all over Minnesota.

35:15.280 --> 35:16.804
- A certain kind of metal,

35:16.840 --> 35:19.172
certain kind of pipe,
certain kind of pipe coating,

35:19.210 --> 35:22.213
so we're checking
all the construction sites
that use that kind of pipe.

35:22.250 --> 35:24.218
- What are we looking for?

35:24.250 --> 35:26.616
- At this stage,
anything really. But mostly,

35:26.650 --> 35:29.153
anything peculiar.

35:34.730 --> 35:37.198
- Two fellas from the FBI.

35:37.230 --> 35:39.790
They goin' through
the drawers now.

35:39.830 --> 35:42.537
Mm-hmm. Puttin' papers
in file boxes.

35:42.570 --> 35:45.767
Yes, they are
takin' things.

35:45.810 --> 35:48.506
No. Well,
they didn't say--

35:48.540 --> 35:50.770
Yes, they can.

35:50.810 --> 35:53.199
What did you say
your names were?

35:54.820 --> 35:56.742
- Garrett Jacob Hobbs?

35:56.780 --> 36:00.181
- He's one of our pipe
threaders. Those are all
the resignation letters.

36:00.220 --> 36:03.883
Plumbers' Union requires 'em
whenever members finish a job.

36:03.920 --> 36:05.956
(whispering): I'll
call you back.

36:05.990 --> 36:09.824
- Uh, does Mr. Hobbs
have a daughter?
- Might have.

36:09.860 --> 36:13.899
- Eighteen or 19, wind-chafed,
uh, plain but pretty.

36:13.930 --> 36:17.639
She'd have auburn hair,
about this tall.
- Maybe.

36:17.670 --> 36:20.230
I don't know. I don't keep
company with these people.

36:20.270 --> 36:22.977
- What is it
about Garrett Jacob Hobbs

36:23.010 --> 36:24.602
you find so peculiar?

36:24.650 --> 36:27.369
- He left a phone number,
no address.

36:27.410 --> 36:30.277
- And therefore he has
something to hide?

36:30.320 --> 36:32.311
- The others all left
addresses.

36:34.520 --> 36:36.909
Do you have an address
for Mr. Hobbs?

36:45.500 --> 36:47.263
I got it.

37:03.950 --> 37:06.418
(phone ringing)

37:09.490 --> 37:11.583
- Hello?

37:11.630 --> 37:13.586
Just a second. Dad.

37:13.630 --> 37:15.621
It's for you.

37:15.660 --> 37:17.025
- Who is it?

37:17.060 --> 37:19.392
- Caller ID said it was...

37:21.400 --> 37:23.789
- Hello?

37:23.840 --> 37:26.604
- [Mr. Garrett Jacob Hobbs?]

37:26.640 --> 37:28.369
- Yeah.

37:28.410 --> 37:31.004
- You don't know me
and I suspect we'll never meet.

37:31.040 --> 37:33.975
This is a courtesy call.
Listen very carefully.

37:37.620 --> 37:39.645
Are you listening?

37:39.690 --> 37:41.851
- Yes.

37:43.690 --> 37:45.885
- They know.

38:01.610 --> 38:04.807
(sound muted)
(soft ambient pulse)

38:16.890 --> 38:18.858
(Sound returns.)

38:18.890 --> 38:20.858
(birds singing)

38:20.890 --> 38:22.994
(rattling)

38:42.820 --> 38:46.415
-Ah... ah!

39:07.070 --> 39:09.971
- Garrett Jacob Hobbs! FBI!

39:13.910 --> 39:16.947
(girl whimpering)

39:22.620 --> 39:25.453
(gunshot)

39:38.570 --> 39:40.936
No, no, no.

39:44.080 --> 39:46.048
- See?

39:46.080 --> 39:48.071
See?

39:56.920 --> 39:58.626
(girl coughing and gasping)

39:58.660 --> 40:00.423
No, no, no.

40:50.940 --> 40:54.717
- (Alana): ...biting in lesser
assaults and bar fights,
child abuse...

40:54.750 --> 40:57.913
Emergency room personnel may be
very helpful that way.

40:57.950 --> 41:01.954
If they have any memories
of bad bites, no matter who was

41:01.990 --> 41:03.548
bitten or h--

41:03.590 --> 41:07.219
**

41:07.260 --> 41:08.796
- Where's Graham?

41:10.260 --> 41:12.865
- You said he wouldn't
get too close.

41:17.700 --> 41:22.979
**

